import React, { useState } from "react";
import Button from "react-bootstrap/Button";
import Form from "react-bootstrap/Form";
import Modal from "react-bootstrap/Modal";

function AddEmpModal({ showAddEmp, handleAddEmpClose, firstName, lastName, emailId, contactNo }) {
	return (
		<Modal show={showAddEmp} onHide={handleAddEmpClose} backdrop="static">
			<Modal.Header closeButton>
				<Modal.Title>Add an Employee</Modal.Title>
			</Modal.Header>
			<Modal.Body>
				<Form>
					<Form.Group className="mb-3" controlId="addEmpForm.ControlInput1">
						<Form.Label>First Name</Form.Label>
						<Form.Control type="text" placeholder="John" autoFocus />
					</Form.Group>
					<Form.Group className="mb-3" controlId="addEmpForm.ControlInput2">
						<Form.Label>Last Name</Form.Label>
						<Form.Control type="text" placeholder="Doe" />
					</Form.Group>
					<Form.Group className="mb-3" controlId="addEmpForm.ControlInput3">
						<Form.Label>Email address</Form.Label>
						<Form.Control type="email" placeholder="name@example.com" />
					</Form.Group>
					<Form.Group className="mb-3" controlId="addEmpForm.ControlInput4">
						<Form.Label>Contact No.</Form.Label>
						<Form.Control type="number" placeholder="John" />
					</Form.Group>
				</Form>
			</Modal.Body>
			<Modal.Footer>
				<Button variant="secondary" onClick={handleAddEmpClose}>
					Close
				</Button>
				<Button variant="primary" onClick={handleAddEmpClose}>
					Save Changes
				</Button>
			</Modal.Footer>
		</Modal>
	);
}

export default AddEmpModal;
